As for the people from TP Coinfist ... it was the guild leader of Celestial Temple and the leader's mate.  And yes I have known for longer than this that you were from Tholuxe Paells as I had talked with other people about my old server as Oogmog said before.  As for going into the details of what they said of you I won't because I don't know them to be true I simply said that your usage of AS and FnF as &quot;reasons&quot; to wake the sleeper made them more believable as it seemed before that you weren't as bad as they said.<br>
<br>
You want to know why I left League of Shadows?  Which time?  I mean I can give you my point of view of every guild I was in just so you can find out.<br>
<br>
Blackened Roses (guild I started)- We lost 80% of our members to not being able to log on after Luclin so I had supported a consolidation with League of Shadows.  A few people decided to stay and I felt it wasn't in the best interest of guild or myself to stay so I joined League of Shadows.<br>
<br>
League of Shadows-  Joined as an officer and went right through the time where our leader disappeared (RL sucks) and weathered through the LoS/ES split.  Later when things started stabilizing and some of the older officers returned my RP interfered with another officers RP and after a heated discussion in which she felt that she was being insulted I left to be a solo person.<br>
<br>
Dark Affliction- Edea who I had been friends with asked me to join them and kept asking telling me that DA was going to be a great guild.  I decided to join but had to go to spring break for a week.  When I came back DA had split into two and Edea asked me to help and rebuild.  I stayed in DA for a long time but when Edea disappeared and many others left I did likewise as I didn't want to further watch the guild crumble ... I rejoined LoS after a discussion with the officer I had the heated arguement with and we both apologized.<br>
<br>
LoS (Part 2)- Plain and simply most of the guild had a different mindset than me.  We also had recently lost our highest level (although Blood rejoined) and I wanted to have fun.  Taking a full group and camping bugs in Seb or other relatively easy things I had been doing for around 3 months got boring to me because of the lack of challenge.  I left simply to pursue a chance to regain the thrill of the challenge.<br>
<br>
FnF- It was a choice between FnF and Reso as I actually had both sides talking to me about joining.  With FnF I had known most of them for a long time although I had a lot of friends in Reso also.  When it simply came down to it I chose the guild with the lower numbers simply because I saw it as more of a challenge.<br>
<br>
